The SABC is going ahead with wide-scale job cuts in a bid to slash costs at the cash-strapped broadcaster. It will also be closing down five offices. Phase 1 of the plan requires all group executives to present plans to their executive directors by the first week of August on how to cut personnel costs by 30%. This is expected to shave R279m a year in costs. Phase 1 also includes a “report to the shareholder on pending retrenchments”. Read the full story in the Sunday Times.